At least three attackers were killed and 10 people wounded on Friday night when a group of terrorists opened fire at a police building in Karachi, the capital of south Pakistan's Sindh province, police and hospital officials said. The attack took place at around 7:10 p.m. local time when eight to 10 terrorists opened fire and hurled hand grenades at the Karachi police chief's office near the Saddar area of Karachi, Deputy Inspector General of south zone Karachi Irfan Baloch told media.